Ukraine received from NATO hardware and software worth ‚Ç¨ 1 million to ensure cyber defense 
Within the first stage of cooperation with the Ukraine-NATO Trust Fund in the field of cyber defense, Ukraine received technical equipment and software worth ‚Ç¨ 1 million, the head of the SBU Vasily Hrytsak said. 
The Romanian side carried out tender procedures and, as of July 1, 2017, supplied to Ukraine the technical equipment and software provided. The received funds are deployed on the basis of the SBU, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Ukraine and the State Communications Committee, they are being integrated into the infrastructure of the national cybersecurity system.
